post1: Long awaited catch up with life long friends!  Why has it taken so long? It was so good to catch up with everybody.  It has been so great seeing how we have all changed and grown both physically and spiritually.  Let me know who is up for making this an annual event? Please let me know.  I am happy to organise it.  Feeling blessed.  Cheers everyone!
post2:
Happy birthday to the best and most wonderful husband I could ever ask for xx  Thank you for everything you do. Thank you for being an awesome dad to our two children. Enjoy your day and look forward the birthday celebrations tonight.  Enjoy your gifts. 
 You  so deserve them.  Love as always.

It’s crazy how some things never change, like our inside jokes and silly stories. Grateful for these friendships that stand the test of time! Can’t wait for the next reunion!
post2: Happy birthday to the love of my life! You bring so much joy and laughter into my world, and I’m endlessly grateful for every moment we share. Your kindness, strength, and passion inspire me every day. Here’s to celebrating you today and all the amazing adventures ahead! Can’t wait to spoil you and make this day unforgettable. Love you to the moon and back!

The room was full of laughter and hugs and kisses as we all remembered the school days. we had a laugh and caught up with all the news about our families and planned the next catch up.
post2: So my darling hubbie, the big day has come - the big 50. Half a century , wow who would have thought it. We have know each other for 33 years of that time, where has it gone. A few more grey hairs and wrinkles between us but we have 2 lovely kids and a great family. Happy Birthday!
